<error-message-context>

<title>Error Message Context and Fix Suggestions</title>

<rules>
- Always include what the user was attempting to accomplish when an error occurs
- Provide the specific action or command that triggered the error
- Include relevant context like file paths, function names, or variable values
- Suggest at least one concrete fix or next step to resolve the error
- Frame suggestions as actionable steps the user can take
- Reference documentation or resources when applicable
- Never assume the user knows why the error occurred
- Keep error explanations concise but complete
</rules>

<examples>
<example type="good">
```
Error: Cannot read property 'length' of undefined

Context: While trying to process the user list in getUserCount(), the 'users' array was undefined.

Suggested fix: Check if the 'users' array exists before accessing its length:
if (users && users.length) {
  return users.length;
}
```
</example>

<example type="good">
```
Error: Permission denied when running 'npm install'

Context: You were trying to install dependencies for the project in /usr/local/project.

Suggested fixes:
1. Run with sudo: `sudo npm install`
2. Change npm's default directory to avoid permission issues
3. Check if you have write permissions to the current directory
```
</example>

<example type="bad">
```
Error: TypeError: Cannot read property 'length' of undefined
```
</example>
</examples>

</error-message-context>